# Analysis of Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
The structure consists of 12 building blocks arranged in 4 layers:
- 3 yellow horizontal rectangular blocks forming the top, middle, and bottom supports
- 4 cube blocks (2 blue and 2 red) arranged in two columns
- 2 green vertical rectangular blocks running the height of the structure

## Spatial Relationships
- Layer 1 (Bottom): Yellow horizontal rectangular block as the base
- Layer 2: Green vertical rectangular block on the left side, blue cube on the right with red cube beneath it
- Layer 3: Yellow horizontal rectangular block in the middle connecting the structures
- Layer 4: Green vertical rectangular block on the right side, blue cube on the left with red cube beneath it
- Layer 5 (Top): Yellow horizontal rectangular block as the top

# Block Selection from Dictionary

Based on the main image, I need the following blocks:
- Yellow horizontal rectangular blocks (indexes 11, 11, 11)
- Blue cubes (indexes 1, 1)
- Red cubes (indexes 3, 3)
- Green vertical rectangular blocks (indexes 7, 8)

# Assembly Order

```
{
   Step1: Move block with index 11
   Step2: Move block with index 7
   Step3: Move block with index 1
   Step4: Move block with index 3
   Step5: Move block with index 11
   Step6: Move block with index 8
   Step7: Move block with index 1
   Step8: Move block with index 3
   Step9: Move block with index 11
}
```
